    <stitle>INSTRUMENTS - TACHOMETER - MANUAL PROGRAMMING</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="install" graphiccount="2">
        <title>MANUAL PROGRAMMING</title>
        <svcprocinfo>
            <para>The tachometer programming DIP switches are located at the top edge on the back of the cluster,
                <hotlnk xrefid="f0803414">Figure 14</hotlnk>
                . The DIP switches are accessed by removing the cluster from the dash (refer to
                <hotlnk document="s08034x_5.xml" xrefid="x0803401">INSTRUMENT CLUSTER, Removal</hotlnk>). Switches 4, 5
                and 6 on the right hand switch bank control tachometer programming (Item 6,
                <hotlnk xrefid="f0803414">Figure 14</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f0803414" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g0803414" filename="../figg08/G0803414.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Speedometer/Tachometer Calibration Switches</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>SWITCH 1. LEFT SIDE DIP SWITCH BANK</callout1>
                    <callout1>SWITCH 2. RIGHT SIDE DIP SWITCH BANK</callout1>
                    <callout1>1. CLUSTER</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. WIRING HARNESS CONNECTORS</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. DIP SWITCHES</callout1>
                    <callout1>4. TEN SPEEDOMETER SETTING SWITCHES (1-8 ON LEFT, 1-2 ON RIGHT)</callout1>
                    <callout1>5. ONE AXLE RATIO SETTING SWITCH (3 ON RIGHT)</callout1>
                    <callout1>6. THREE TACHOMETER SETTING SWITCHES (4-5-6 ON RIGHT)</callout1>
                    <callout1>7. ONE TACHOMETER RANGE SWITCH (7 ON RIGHT) 0=3500 RPM, 1=2500 RPM (REV. C91) 1=3000 RPM
                        (REV. C92)
                    </callout1>
                    <callout1>8. ONE ENGLISH-METRIC CONVERSION SWITCH (8 ON RIGHT)</callout1>
                    <callout1>Note: UP = 1 DOWN = 0</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <specpara>
                <important>
                    <para>Switch 7 (Item 10,
                        <hotlnk xrefid="f0803414">Figure 14</hotlnk>) in the right bank controls the range of RPM
                        readings. This switch is
                        <emph type="boldundersc">always set at 0</emph>
                        to give the 0-3500 RPM readings. If the tachometer is giving erroneous readings, check this
                        switch setting.
                    </para>
                </important>
            </specpara>
        </svcprocinfo>
